        "email": "adilger@thelustrecollective.com",
        "username": "adilger"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-16 01:45:43.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: I would prefer that you didn't submit this\n\nJC, this should really be moved to lustre_user.h instead of lustre_idl.h, since lustre_idl.h isn't directly usable by applications.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
    {
      "id": "ddedd92ebbac314b7c919ac275817f19d1fab2d5",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 140,
        "name": "jacques-Charles Lafoucriere",
        "email": "jacques-charles.lafoucriere@cea.fr",
        "username": "jcl"
      },
      "date": "2013-05-16 08:21:30.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nI used lustre_idl because this is where lov_mds_md is declared. lustre_user declares lov_user_md.\nSo do I make a new function lov_user_md_size() and leave lov_mds_md_size in lustre_idl (ie for kernel use) ?\nDo you confirm lov_user_md is the right interface from user space (even with setxattr as it is done in LU-2182)",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 1
    },
